# .trivyignore — Trivy scan suppressions for intentional infrastructure decisions
#
# Each suppressed rule is documented with the rationale. Re-evaluate when
# infra topology changes (e.g., if public gRPC/HTTPS ports are moved behind
# a load balancer or API gateway, or if TigerBeetle drops its hostNetwork req).

# ── TigerBeetle StatefulSet ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# KSV-0009: hostNetwork=true required for TigerBeetle VSR inter-replica consensus.
#   TigerBeetle explicitly rejects DNS hostnames and uses raw node IPs for its
#   Viewstamped Replication protocol. Changing this breaks TB cluster formation.
#   File: infra/k8s/base/tigerbeetle/statefulset.yaml
#   Owner: infra team | Last reviewed: 2026-05-23
KSV-0009

# KSV-0014: TigerBeetle data container must write journal + data files to
#   /data (PVC-backed) and uses runtime temp paths at startup. Setting
#   readOnlyRootFilesystem=true breaks the TB storage engine.
#   All other workloads (banking/crypto/payments/trading/grafana/prometheus/
#   init-replica-id) explicitly set readOnlyRootFilesystem: true.
#   File: infra/k8s/base/tigerbeetle/statefulset.yaml (tigerbeetle container only)
#   Owner: infra team | Last reviewed: 2026-05-23
KSV-0014

# ── DigitalOcean Terraform Firewall ──────────────────────────────────────────
#
# DIG-0001: Public gRPC (:50050) and HTTPS (:443/:80) ingress open to
#   0.0.0.0/0 is intentional — Blazil is an internet-facing API service and
#   these ports must be reachable from clients globally.
#   The SSH management rule (line 80) uses var.management_cidr; Trivy cannot
#   evaluate Terraform variable values so it defaults to 0.0.0.0/0 —
#   this is a false positive; the variable restricts access to a named CIDR.
#   Owner: infra team | Last reviewed: 2026-05-23
DIG-0001

# DIG-0003: Outbound internet egress to 0.0.0.0/0 is required for:
#   - TLS/HTTPS certificate validation and renewal (Let's Encrypt)
#   - DNS resolution to upstream resolvers
#   - Connectivity to external financial services (exchanges, payment rails)
#   - OS package updates and security patches
#   Owner: infra team | Last reviewed: 2026-05-23
DIG-0003

# ── Third-party Upstream Submodule (core/aeron-sys/aeron) ────────────────────
#
# DS-0015: yum package cache not cleaned in Rocky Linux builder Dockerfile.
#   File: core/aeron-sys/aeron/cppbuild/rocky/Dockerfile
#   This is UPSTREAM code from real-logic/aeron tag 1.50.4 — a C++ build
#   environment Dockerfile, NOT a runtime production image.  We do not own
#   this repo and cannot push fixes to it; the submodule must stay pinned to
#   the upstream tag.  The image is only used to build the aeron_static.a
#   library on Rocky Linux CI agents — it is never deployed or used at runtime.
#   Owner: infra team | Last reviewed: 2026-05-23
DS-0015

